---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 996c9a12-d13d-4597-a783-506d70cd1736
Verse: 72
Translator: Jonathan Barnes
Book: Early Greek Philosophy
Publisher: Penguin Books
Copyright: 1987
---
Most are at odds with that with which they most constantly associate --
the account which governs the universe -- and ... what they meet with
every day seems foreign to them.
